    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 20th level, your ancestorâ€™s act of martyrdom infuses your spirit. You become immune to death effects. Material&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Components\">components</a>&nbsp;for spells and effects to bring you back to life (such as @Compendium[pf1.spells.c5anior2ysy6s2xy]{Raise Dead}&nbsp;or @Compendium[pf1.spells.thh46ghi51lrl3cl]{Resurrection}) cost half as much as normal. Your body cannot be turned into an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Undead\">undead</a>&nbsp;creature, as though you were affected by a permanent @Compendium[pf1.spells.vxmp5prgw5fj4h6f]{Hallow}&nbsp;effect (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic#TOC-Caster-Level\">caster level</a>&nbsp;equal to your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/sorcerer\">sorcerer</a>&nbsp;level).</p>",
